      "title": "A cow escaped a slaughterhouse and hid for 40 days",
      "content_html": "<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/20/emily-the-cow.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"A cow escaped a slaughterhouse and hid for 40 days\"><img alt=\"Emily the cow — Daderot / CC0 (via Wikipedia)\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"1669\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Animal_Rights_Memorial_-_Sherborn2C_Massachusetts_-_DSC02932_28cropped_229.jpg?fit=2507%2C1669&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"2507\" /></a><p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Minutes before she was to be killed at a slaughterhouse in Hopkinton, Massachusetts, a three-year-old, 1,600-pound heifer named <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emily_(cow)\">Emily</a> cleared the five-foot gate and ran. She stayed loose for 40 days through record snowfall in the winter of 1995, foraging in backyards and, at times, running with a herd of deer. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/20/emily-the-cow.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/20/emily-the-cow.html\">A cow escaped a slaughterhouse and hid for 40 days</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
